{"search_data": "JharkhandJharkhand Unemployment Allowance | Farm Loan Waiver Scheme Announced in Budget 2020-21Jharkhand govt. announces Farm Loan Waiver Scheme (loans upto Rs. 50,000 to be waived off) for farmers & unemployment allowance scheme in Budget 2020-21, jobless youth registered with employment exchenge for job will get Rs. 5,000 for graduate & Rs. 7,000 for post-graduationJharkhand Unemployment Allowance | Farm Loan Waiver Scheme 2020Jharkhand Budget 2020-21 is presented in the state assembly at an estimated cost of Rs. 86,370 crore. The revenue and capital expenditure is estimated at Rs. 73,316 crore and Rs. 13,054 crore respectively. Around 75% of total Jharkhand population depends on agriculture and allied activities. The state govt. of Jharkhand is determined for the development of people associated with farming sector and thus will start Farm Loan Waiver Scheme. Moreover to tackle unemployment, all the job-less youths will get unemployment allowance.Jharkhand government has decided to start a short-term farm loan waiver scheme for farmers whose income share goes in repaying farm loan. In the 1st phase of Jharkhand Kisan Karj Mafi Yojana 2020-21, farm loans upto Rs. 50,000 will be waived. The state govt. will assess the total number of farmers who had taken loan and total amount that needs to be repaid. Another major budgetary provision has been made for those people who consumes less than 300 units of power. Such people will not have to pay any electricity dues for first 100 units.The state govt. will provide unemployment allowance of Rs. 5,000 p.a (for 2 years) to all those unemployed youths who had earned their bachelor degree (graduation) in last 3 years. Moreover, govt. will also provide Rs. 7,000 to all those jobless candidates who earned their masters\u2019 degree (post-graduation) in past 3 years. All the Jharkhand unemployment allowance scheme beneficiaries are required to be registered with employment exchange for jobs. The state government has made budgetary provision of Rs. 146 crore.The state govt. of Jharkhand is also going to provide universal scholarship for students enrolled in government schools from Class 1st to 12th under the Chief Minister Special Student Scholarship scheme. All those families who annual income is less than Rs. 8 lakh will now get free treatment for critical illness such as cancer and kidney and liver ailments in top-notch health institutions of the country. CM also announced to provide an additional amount of Rs. 50,000 to PM Awas Yojana beneficiaries. Ration would also be provided to 10 lakh people above 50 years of age.  Sarkari Yojana App - Download Now Source / Reference Link: https://www.thehindu.com/news/national/other-states/jharkhand-govt-announces-farm-loan-waiver-unemployment-dole/article30975676.ece  at  "}